mmary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing dependency relevance**\\n\\nIt seems that the extra dependency isn't strictly necessary. I’m thinking about the current generated setup mechanism, which might not even be relevant. The user has specified not to apply certain changes, so maybe we can provide advisory preparation with the dependency only if the normal generated scaffold fails to import the upstream test helper. I should examine the deterministic_setup entries to see how they can apply before generation, particularly regarding dependency or docket issues. Including test-values could be beneficial, but there are risks with the test artifact version.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_tcR0kszTlA0z8iD9KGFPFcZm|fc_0f2e0b9bbbbedd95016a3f07b4e0948194ba87dce8d03fa620", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "curl -fsI https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/neo4j/bolt/neo4j-bolt-connection-test-values/4.0.0/neo4j-bolt-connection-test-values-4.0.0.jar | head -5\ncurl -fsSL https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/neo4j/bolt/neo4j-bolt-connection-test-values/4.0.0/neo4j-bolt-connection-test-values-4.0.0.pom | grep -E '<artifactId>|<version>|<scope>' | head -40", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 7529, "output": 669, "cacheRead": 62976, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 71174, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782515626380, "responseId": "resp_0f2e0b9bbbbedd95016a3f07aaee1c8194856a0eb6f5be2ae3"}}
